  "prompt": "How do you convert gallons to ounces?",
  "response": "To convert gallons to ounces, you can use the conversion factor that 1 gallon is equal to 128 ounces. \n\nThe formula to convert gallons to ounces is:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Ounces} = \\text{Gallons} \\times 128\n\\]\n\nSo, if you have a specific number of gallons, just multiply it by 128 to get the equivalent amount in ounces. \n\nFor example, if you have 2 gallons:\n\n\\[\n2 \\text{ gallons} \\times 128 = 256 \\text{ ounces}\n\\]",
